data.text:
Story

DJ Blackout got his start in Djing at the age of sixteen performing for local house parties and for high schools throughout the Los Angeles area. He then continued in his pursuit and passion for music at California State University, Fresno. With his financial aid refund check he decided to purchase a sound system in hopes of making money Djing events for student, staff, local clubs and Greek Letter Organizations. As a freshman he was offered to work for the Fresno State Men’s Division I Basketball Team as an assistant manager to the Audio/Video Technician. His talent led Blackout to Dj for his close friends that he built a personal and business relationship with over the years. He has had the opportunity to spin for collegiate friend Paul George of the Indiana Pacers at his draft party with footage provided by SkiTV, Rapper Glasses Malone, and other Celebrity Private Events.

Achievements

1. Worked with Y.G.’s producer DJ Mustard, who has produced songs for Tyga’s “Rack City”, Skeme’s “T.O. featuring Problem”, and many other top selling artists.

2. Holds broad musical talents such as playing the violin

3. Produces multiple music genres.

4. Dj’d for the city of Fresno Deaf Center (D.H.H.S.C).

5. Has Dj’d at two dozen Universities throughout California.

6. Dj’d events with YMCMB artist Glasses Malone.

7. Also worked with the Legendary Female DJ and Funk Master Flex’s Big Dog Pitbull Member, as well as DJ Jazzy Joyce on her show, “Keeping it Jazzy with Joyce”, in the Bronx, NY as her main DJ.

8. Dj’d for a list of NBA players including 2012 NBA dunk contest participant Paul George.
